The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Thursday, August 29, 2002  Weight favours Adamile 
 FROM WILLIAM TELL				 										Mysore: The two horses most likely to battle it out for the 1,400m H. H. Sri Krishnaraja Wadiyar Memorial Gold Cup, a terms race here on Thursday are Bold Chieftan and Adamile. Bold are in top condition. They met twice during the Bangalore summer with Bold Chieftan finishing ahead on both oacasions. However, with Adamile being better off at weights this time out, the Darius Byramji-ward, to be piloted by Pesi Shroff is tipped to win.				 										SELECTIONS				 										1.15 pm: Worldly Pick 1. Random Hearts 2. Royal Satsuma 3. 				 										1.45 pm: Turf Rythm 1. Me And Mine 2. Beautiful Bird 3.				 										2.15 pm: Amber Regent 1. Milan 2. Air Strike 3. 				 										2.45 pm: Acquire 1. Priceless Accord 2. Queen Of Angels 3.				 										3.15 pm: Falconet 1. Secret Silver 2. Limitations 3.				 										3.45 pm: Sacristia 1. Forest Rose 2. Pretty Move 3.				 										4.15 pm: Adamile 1. Bold Chieftan 2. Taipan 3.				 										4.45 pm: Attorney 1. Extreme Bondage 2. Streak Of Fire 3.				 										5.15 pm: Prophecy 1. Silver Victress 2. Brave Risk 3.				 										Days Best: Amber Regent Double: Acquire amp; Falconet
